      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "With a string length of <code>211900000</code>, time taken to complete <code>for (char c : str.toCharArray()) { }</code> is ~250ms and time taken to complete <code>for (char c : charArray) { }</code> is &lt;10ms. Of course, these time values will depend on the hardware but the takeaway is that one method is significantly costly than the other."
