  "title" : "How do I apply the for-each loop to every character in a String?",
  "body" : "<p>So I want to iterate for each character in a string.</p>\n\n<p>So I thought:</p>\n\n<pre><code>for (char c : \"xyz\")\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>but I get a compiler error:</p>\n\n<pre><code>MyClass.java:20: foreach not applicable to expression type\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>How can I do this?</p>\n"
